One week into BHM ❤️✊🏽 a quote that I love and I think it’s cute considering it’s almost Valentine’s Day… Have a great day everyone 💋

To the love of my life, you found me, I cherished you, shared years with you, changed with you, and lost you. 
Serendipitously, humorously, and clunk-ily- kinda sorta found you again on this new road. aaannnddd lost you. 
Again. 

I lost you a lot this year. I lost a lot this year. 

To the love of my life, you left me a ghost. Hallow. Dark. 
Missing that guiding spark. Accepting that this was going to be my way of life now. Just a ghost who’s only way for me to join life again was passively. Only to host. 
I didn’t want to move on from my past life and the ways I lived. Trying so hard to look at my life and wonder why I died the way that I did. Haunting.
Why you did you have to be the cause of my death? Why did you take everything with you? How do I come back to life from this? Could I come to life after this? How do I make sense of things that you left paranormal? 
Is the most that I become is a vampire? 

Deeply craving, thirsting, hunting for that spark on the inside to come back to me.
Ripping myself apart. 

To the love of my life, the tearing of myself, I found breath. Breath that gave. Gave the ability to bring my own self back from the dead. I found myself embracing the entire. Being called higher. And truly being grateful for the love that I aspire.
And yes, as corny as that last line is, you brought me a gift. 
A gift in the smallest moments where you find breath. In people, places, things. Whirlwinds. 

You brought me a gift that I.
That I. am still learning to cherish. That I am still learning to breathe. 
A love of my life. 
.

. 

. 
I really do love this day. 
To the people who made my year way more loving.
